The `eLpNorm` of a function `f` with respect to measure `őľ` and exponent `p` is defined as the `p`-th root of the integral of `f^p` with respect to `őľ`. When `őľ F = 0`, the set `F` is negligible with respect to `őľ`. The function `F.indicator (fun _ ‚Ü¶ 1)` is `1` on `F` and `0` elsewhere. Since `F` is negligible, `T (F.indicator (fun _ ‚Ü¶ 1))` is `T` applied to a function that is zero almost everywhere with respect to `őĹ.restrict G`. Therefore, `T (F.indicator (fun _ ‚Ü¶ 1))` is zero almost everywhere with respect to `őĹ.restrict G`, making its `eLpNorm` zero.

