We need to show `eLpNorm (T (F.indicator (fun _ ‚Ü¶ 1))) 1 (őĹ.restrict G) ‚Č§ c * (őľ F) ^ p‚ĀĽ¬Ļ.toReal * (őĹ G) ^ p'‚ĀĽ¬Ļ.toReal`.
If `¬¨(őĹ G < ‚ąě)`, then `‚ąě ‚Č§ őĹ G`. This means `G` is `őĹ`-null.
So `T (F.indicator (fun _ ‚Ü¶ 1))` is `T (F.indicator 1)`.
Since `G` is `őĹ`-null, the `eLpNorm` is 0. So LHS is 0.
RHS is `c * (őľ F) ^ p‚ĀĽ¬Ļ.toReal * (őĹ G) ^ p'‚ĀĽ¬Ļ.toReal`.
Since `¬¨(őĹ G < ‚ąě)`, `őĹ G ‚Č• ‚ąě`. So `(őĹ G) ^ p'‚ĀĽ¬Ļ.toReal ‚Č• (‚ąě) ^ p'‚ĀĽ¬Ļ.toReal`.
If `p'‚ĀĽ¬Ļ.toReal > 0`, then `(‚ąě) ^ p'‚ĀĽ¬Ļ.toReal = ‚ąě`.
So RHS ‚Č• `c * ... * ‚ąě = ‚ąě` (if c > 0).
So `0 ‚Č§ ‚ąě` holds.

